WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

00:01:33.080 --> 00:01:34.080
Let's see where you can run.

00:01:34.080 --> 00:01:35.120
Get up.

00:01:42.160 --> 00:01:42.890
Are you okay?

00:01:43.360 --> 00:01:44.120
Are you okay?

00:01:44.840 --> 00:01:45.570
Are you okay?

00:01:50.759 --> 00:01:51.479
Brother.

00:02:02.600 --> 00:02:03.400
Let's go home.

00:02:04.080 --> 00:02:04.760
Let's go.

00:02:06.640 --> 00:02:07.440
Take it easy.

00:02:12.920 --> 00:02:13.650
Are you done?

00:02:15.480 --> 00:02:16.210
Who's there?

00:02:16.720 --> 00:02:17.120
What are you doing?

00:02:17.120 --> 00:02:17.840
Go.

00:02:18.200 --> 00:02:19.130
Stop! Don't run!

00:02:19.400 --> 00:02:19.880
Stop!

00:02:19.960 --> 00:02:20.560
Xiaoling.

00:02:22.160 --> 00:02:23.120
Hurry up.

00:02:23.600 --> 00:02:24.460
Go. Don't move.

00:02:25.840 --> 00:02:26.440
Get down.

00:02:26.960 --> 00:02:28.840
Get down.

00:02:29.720 --> 00:02:30.850
Why are you running?

00:02:39.520 --> 00:02:40.120
Brother.

00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:42.820
Caught three people putting up posters.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:46.280
This is a cultural institution

00:02:46.280 --> 00:02:47.280
founded by Mr. Schirle, a German.

00:02:47.280 --> 00:02:47.920
According to the agreement,

00:02:47.920 --> 00:02:49.079
you need written authorization from the German Embassy

00:02:49.079 --> 00:02:50.600
or Mr. Schirle

00:02:50.600 --> 00:02:51.730
to conduct a search.

00:02:53.560 --> 00:02:55.760
Search them and see what else they have.

00:02:56.240 --> 00:02:56.840
Search.

00:02:58.480 --> 00:02:59.120
Behave.

00:03:05.560 --> 00:03:06.120
Brother.

00:03:14.760 --> 00:03:16.360
Why are you out putting up posters

00:03:16.360 --> 00:03:18.020
instead of sleeping at night?

00:03:19.280 --> 00:03:20.680
Resisting the Japanese.

00:03:22.920 --> 00:03:24.040
Do you think you few

00:03:24.440 --> 00:03:26.000
can curse the Japanese to death

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:27.200
just by talking

00:03:28.360 --> 00:03:29.960
and putting up a few posters?

00:03:30.600 --> 00:03:33.130
If so, they would have been wiped out long ago.

00:03:33.560 --> 00:03:34.200
Get out.

00:03:37.079 --> 00:03:37.840
You mean it?

00:03:38.200 --> 00:03:38.920
Really.

00:03:40.040 --> 00:03:40.900
Get out of here.

00:03:42.640 --> 00:03:43.280
Let's go.

00:03:45.720 --> 00:03:46.400
Stop.

00:03:49.520 --> 00:03:51.050
You don't want your things?

00:04:00.760 --> 00:04:01.620
Just this once.

00:04:01.840 --> 00:04:03.100
It won't happen again.

00:04:06.120 --> 00:04:06.720
Let's go.

00:04:14.720 --> 00:04:15.320
Brother.

00:04:15.720 --> 00:04:17.649
There are no secrets in this world.

00:04:17.720 --> 00:04:19.480
If Section Chief Qian asks tomorrow,

00:04:19.480 --> 00:04:20.440
how do we explain this?

00:04:20.440 --> 00:04:21.160
Idiot.

00:04:22.240 --> 00:04:23.320
Putting up posters

00:04:23.320 --> 00:04:24.640
isn't like murder or arson.

00:04:24.640 --> 00:04:26.640
It's more like urinating in public.

00:04:26.640 --> 00:04:27.600
You've been with me for so many years.

00:04:27.600 --> 00:04:29.130
Do I still need to teach you?

00:04:29.720 --> 00:04:30.560
Let's go.

00:04:44.800 --> 00:04:45.680
Do you know what would have happened to you

00:04:45.680 --> 00:04:46.760
if the Special Branch had caught you

00:04:46.760 --> 00:04:48.120
today?

00:04:48.560 --> 00:04:50.220
You would have lost your life.

00:04:54.200 --> 00:04:56.000
You're grown up now, aren't you?

00:04:56.240 --> 00:04:58.170
I can't control you anymore, can I?

00:04:58.200 --> 00:05:00.200
Didn't you cry for freedom all day long?

00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:01.330
Now I'm telling you,

00:05:01.480 --> 00:05:02.800
you are free.

00:05:03.080 --> 00:05:04.800
These are your things. Take them away.

00:05:04.800 --> 00:05:07.130
From now on, I don't have a sister like you.

00:05:10.520 --> 00:05:13.180
Whether you live or die has nothing to do with me.

00:05:18.880 --> 00:05:19.560
Brother.

00:05:20.440 --> 00:05:21.920
Don't be angry.

00:05:23.120 --> 00:05:24.640
Let me be honest with you.

00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:27.040
Do you know?

00:05:28.080 --> 00:05:30.810
How many people in the Anti-Japanese United Army

00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:33.159
we can save by sending a telegram?

00:05:35.440 --> 00:05:37.560
But with every telegram we send out,

00:05:39.040 --> 00:05:40.240
we face

00:05:40.360 --> 00:05:42.440
immense danger and sacrifice.

00:05:52.880 --> 00:05:53.560
Brother.

00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:56.000
Do you know

00:05:56.680 --> 00:05:58.920
why I take such great risks

00:05:58.920 --> 00:05:59.840
to do this?

00:06:00.560 --> 00:06:02.200
Why do so many people

00:06:03.280 --> 00:06:05.320
leave their homes and families behind,

00:06:05.320 --> 00:06:06.720
stepping into the breach

00:06:07.480 --> 00:06:08.920
to embark on this path?

00:06:12.160 --> 00:06:14.840
Because we are resisting the invaders.

00:06:18.800 --> 00:06:20.800
We are protecting our country.

00:06:22.400 --> 00:06:23.880
If the country falls,

00:06:25.280 --> 00:06:27.680
we will all become slaves without a nation.

00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:32.760
Brother,

00:06:34.320 --> 00:06:35.920
don't blame me.

00:06:38.080 --> 00:06:38.800
Brother,

00:06:40.480 --> 00:06:41.880
don't be mad.

00:06:44.800 --> 00:06:45.480
Brother.

00:06:49.360 --> 00:06:50.040
Brother.

00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:53.360
Brother.

00:07:27.360 --> 00:07:28.680
The Japanese came today

00:07:28.680 --> 00:07:30.940
and asked us to promote Manchukuo songs.

00:07:31.600 --> 00:07:33.800
To numb the youth with Manchukuo songs.

00:07:35.440 --> 00:07:36.370
We can't do that.

00:07:40.880 --> 00:07:41.560
Sister Qin.

00:07:42.159 --> 00:07:43.159
I want to hold an open-air concert

00:07:43.159 --> 00:07:44.440
in front of the harmonica club.

00:07:44.440 --> 00:07:46.000
Besides playing 'The Song of the Volga Boatmen',

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:47.520
'Carmen', 'La Dame aux Camelias',

00:07:47.520 --> 00:07:49.240
and 'Autumn Moon over the Calm Lake',

00:07:49.240 --> 00:07:50.720
I also want to play our 'Battlefield Moon'

00:07:50.720 --> 00:07:51.960
and 'Riding the Wind and Waves'

00:07:51.960 --> 00:07:53.020
to awaken the youth

00:07:53.120 --> 00:07:54.680
and unite more cultural figures

00:07:54.680 --> 00:07:56.540
to resist the Japanese together.

00:08:10.440 --> 00:08:11.920
Mr. Wang, you busy?

00:08:12.240 --> 00:08:13.040
You're here.

00:08:13.520 --> 00:08:14.640
Here to support your business again.

00:08:14.640 --> 00:08:15.320
Great.

00:08:15.600 --> 00:08:16.660
Take a look at this,

00:08:16.680 --> 00:08:17.810
it stopped ticking.

00:08:20.560 --> 00:08:21.560
Look at the back,

00:08:21.640 --> 00:08:22.970
is it missing any parts?

00:08:26.480 --> 00:08:28.280
This is quite an antique.

00:08:30.640 --> 00:08:32.600
It's not easy to fix.

00:08:34.919 --> 00:08:36.520
No problem if it can be fixed.

00:08:37.640 --> 00:08:38.640
To fix this clock,

00:08:38.760 --> 00:08:40.220
we need sturdy materials.

00:08:40.320 --> 00:08:41.850
Preferably Japanese ones.

00:08:45.840 --> 00:08:47.160
Tomorrow at this time,

00:08:48.160 --> 00:08:50.820
have the water carrier deliver it to Xitou Well.

00:08:51.280 --> 00:08:52.520
Alright, no problem.

00:08:52.720 --> 00:08:54.120
Thanks for your hard work.

00:08:54.120 --> 00:08:54.580
Take it.

00:08:54.640 --> 00:08:55.280
Thank you.

00:08:55.640 --> 00:08:56.360
I'm leaving.

00:08:56.360 --> 00:08:56.880
Okay.

00:08:57.040 --> 00:08:57.720
Take care.

00:09:00.400 --> 00:09:01.440
Last night,

00:09:01.720 --> 00:09:03.800
the newly built military supply warehouse

00:09:03.800 --> 00:09:05.560
was blown up

00:09:06.200 --> 00:09:08.800
by the Anti-Japanese United Army guerrillas.

00:09:08.960 --> 00:09:11.200
The explosives used by the guerrillas

00:09:11.560 --> 00:09:12.760
are of the same nature

00:09:12.800 --> 00:09:14.960
as the previous

00:09:15.160 --> 00:09:16.290
arsenal explosion.

00:09:16.400 --> 00:09:17.960
It was the underground party's radio again

00:09:17.960 --> 00:09:20.420
that sent intelligence to the assault team.

00:09:20.600 --> 00:09:22.880
The radio station transferred to Xinshi Street

00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:25.140
hasn't transmitted in the past two days.

00:09:26.280 --> 00:09:27.040
Suzuki.

00:09:28.080 --> 00:09:29.960
Did that radio station

00:09:30.200 --> 00:09:31.400
sniff something out?

00:09:31.640 --> 00:09:32.360
Captain.

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:34.480
That underground party radio station

00:09:34.480 --> 00:09:35.840
is very cunning.

00:09:36.040 --> 00:09:37.800
They use mobile transmission

00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:39.200
and burst mode.

00:09:39.640 --> 00:09:40.840
They finish sending the telegram

00:09:40.840 --> 00:09:43.240
within three minutes and stop immediately

00:09:43.680 --> 00:09:46.120
to reduce the probability of being detected.

00:09:46.120 --> 00:09:47.580
It is quite normal for them

00:09:47.800 --> 00:09:49.530
not to transmit for a day or two.

00:09:50.120 --> 00:09:50.920
Captain.

00:09:52.040 --> 00:09:54.080
Mr. Suzuki here is

00:09:54.640 --> 00:09:56.370
a hound in the detection world.

00:09:59.240 --> 00:09:59.920
Sorry.

00:10:00.080 --> 00:10:02.040
This metaphor is not very appropriate.

00:10:02.040 --> 00:10:02.840
Don't mind it.

00:10:04.440 --> 00:10:05.640
I mean,

00:10:06.280 --> 00:10:09.120
can we set a trap

00:10:10.160 --> 00:10:11.240
for this rabbit?

00:10:15.520 --> 00:10:16.450
Tell me about it.

00:10:23.280 --> 00:10:24.280
Heming, Qin,

00:10:24.400 --> 00:10:24.920
Xiaoxiong.

00:10:24.920 --> 00:10:26.380
My eldest brother is here.

00:10:26.680 --> 00:10:27.600
You are all here.

00:10:27.600 --> 00:10:28.560
Mr. Shen,

00:10:28.640 --> 00:10:29.480
sit down and talk.

00:10:29.480 --> 00:10:30.080
Okay.

00:10:36.040 --> 00:10:36.960
I brought you

00:10:37.040 --> 00:10:38.440
the things you asked for.

00:10:38.880 --> 00:10:39.360
Great.

00:10:39.360 --> 00:10:40.000
Wait.

00:10:40.280 --> 00:10:41.360
Before inspecting the goods,

00:10:41.360 --> 00:10:43.000
I must declare one thing.

00:10:43.600 --> 00:10:45.330
From now on, you must consult me

00:10:45.560 --> 00:10:47.620
about anything involving my sister.

00:10:51.240 --> 00:10:52.440
Let's put it this way.

00:10:52.520 --> 00:10:54.560
From now on, I will take care of my sister's affairs,

00:10:54.560 --> 00:10:55.440
and I will see them through

00:10:55.440 --> 00:10:56.400
to the end.

00:11:01.680 --> 00:11:02.940
All right. No problem.

00:11:03.280 --> 00:11:04.640
As for the things on your list,

00:11:04.640 --> 00:11:06.280
except for the vacuum tubes and resistors,

00:11:06.280 --> 00:11:07.280
they are all here.

00:11:07.480 --> 00:11:09.340
I will get them within a day or two.

00:11:09.640 --> 00:11:10.500
You find a place

00:11:10.680 --> 00:11:12.360
to install the transmitter first.

00:11:12.360 --> 00:11:14.200
Let me know where it is then,

00:11:14.600 --> 00:11:16.840
and I will personally deliver the vacuum tubes.

00:11:16.840 --> 00:11:17.400
Okay.

00:11:17.560 --> 00:11:18.690
Thank you, Mr. Shen.

00:11:18.960 --> 00:11:19.600
Thank you.

00:11:20.840 --> 00:11:22.500
All right, inspect the goods.

00:11:25.200 --> 00:11:28.060
Then we can set up more checkpoints on Xinshi Street

00:11:28.440 --> 00:11:30.300
to strictly check those carrying

00:11:30.360 --> 00:11:31.400
resistors

00:11:32.040 --> 00:11:34.040
and vacuum

00:11:34.520 --> 00:11:36.280
tubes.

00:11:37.960 --> 00:11:38.640
This way,

00:11:38.800 --> 00:11:41.160
we can block the route for the underground party

00:11:41.160 --> 00:11:42.890
to transfer the radio station.

00:11:43.080 --> 00:11:45.540
Then our air-ground coordinated detection

00:11:45.840 --> 00:11:47.370
will exert enormous power.

00:11:47.560 --> 00:11:50.040
As long as the underground party uses the radio station,

00:11:50.040 --> 00:11:51.520
they are courting death.

00:11:54.080 --> 00:11:55.200
Before 12:00 noon,

00:11:56.080 --> 00:11:57.800
set up checkpoints at all intersections on Xinshi Street

00:11:57.800 --> 00:11:59.130
for strict inspection.

00:11:59.600 --> 00:12:01.860
Anyone carrying electronic components

00:12:02.160 --> 00:12:03.160
will be arrested.

00:12:03.400 --> 00:12:04.040
Yes, sir.

00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:05.860
It's very good.

00:12:06.760 --> 00:12:08.290
Authentic Japanese goods.

00:12:09.200 --> 00:12:12.040
Isn't Kang Suzuki's air-ground coordination powerful?

00:12:12.040 --> 00:12:12.600
Yes.

00:12:12.600 --> 00:12:14.840
What makes it powerful is its aerial part,

00:12:14.840 --> 00:12:16.760
which is the commanding height of the

00:12:16.760 --> 00:12:18.240
Chinese Eastern Railway Bureau Building.

00:12:18.240 --> 00:12:19.120
The top platform

00:12:19.120 --> 00:12:20.480
is like a watchtower.

00:12:20.840 --> 00:12:21.800
The fixed direction finders

00:12:21.800 --> 00:12:23.400
sweep around 360 degrees.

00:12:23.560 --> 00:12:24.400
So,

00:12:24.520 --> 00:12:25.760
the signals we transmit

00:12:25.760 --> 00:12:26.560
are to them

00:12:26.640 --> 00:12:27.920
like lighting a lantern at night.

00:12:27.920 --> 00:12:30.650
Then where should the transmitter be installed?

00:12:30.840 --> 00:12:31.570
A warehouse.

00:12:32.240 --> 00:12:33.400
There's a warehouse on Xinshi Street

00:12:33.400 --> 00:12:34.720
that is perfectly suitable.

00:12:34.720 --> 00:12:35.280
Okay.

00:12:35.520 --> 00:12:37.650
Let's install the transmitter there.

00:12:39.680 --> 00:12:40.160
Bastard.

00:12:40.160 --> 00:12:41.000
What the hell?

00:12:42.440 --> 00:12:43.440
Have mercy, officers!

00:12:43.440 --> 00:12:44.920
I'm just an honest,

00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:46.400
small business owner.

00:12:46.560 --> 00:12:47.800
I sell sewing supplies

00:12:47.800 --> 00:12:49.320
to pay for my child's medical bills.

00:12:49.320 --> 00:12:50.040
I don't know what's going on.

00:12:50.040 --> 00:12:51.570
Cut the crap. Take him away.

00:12:52.680 --> 00:12:53.440
Get up.

00:12:56.600 --> 00:12:57.440
Mr. Shen.

00:12:57.840 --> 00:12:59.440
Section Chief Qian is here in person.

00:12:59.440 --> 00:13:00.840
What big event has happened?

00:13:00.840 --> 00:13:01.600
Nothing.

00:13:01.720 --> 00:13:03.250
Just a routine inspection.

00:13:04.080 --> 00:13:05.120
Thanks for your hard work.

00:13:05.120 --> 00:13:06.360
Not at all.

00:13:07.840 --> 00:13:10.040
Business has been booming for you lately, Mr. Shen.

00:13:10.040 --> 00:13:12.120
What good stuff are you loading back there?